abstract: Orders from the Republican Party and other conservative groups helped push Mr. Trump’s best-selling book, records show.
snippet: Orders from the Republican Party and other conservative groups helped push Mr. Trump’s best-selling book, records show.
lead_paragraph: Boxes began arriving in early November at the Phoenix headquarters of Turning Point USA, a conservative student group with ties to the Trump family.

abstract: Fred Rogers’s belief that we should validate emotions, not suppress them, is wisdom for all ages.
snippet: Fred Rogers’s belief that we should validate emotions, not suppress them, is wisdom for all ages.
lead_paragraph: On the 51st anniversary of the first taping of the classic children’s show “Mister Rogers’ Neighborhood,” Google published an animated “doodle” commemorating him. It depicts Mister Rogers walking through the neighborhood interacting with a variety of people, including a small child with his head hung low. Rogers fashions a paper airplane for the boy, which instantly cheers him up. People commonly caricature Mister Rogers this way — a gentle man intent on making everyone happy — but that may be more a reflection of America’s discomfort with dark emotions than of the man himself. The last thing Fred Rogers would do for a sad boy is distract him from his sadness.

headline_main: It’s a Terrible Day in the Neighborhood, and That’s O.K.

abstract: A charity store fan says: ‘I make sure it’s absolutely impeccable, and I wrap it impeccably. And maybe I don’t tell them.’
snippet: A charity store fan says: ‘I make sure it’s absolutely impeccable, and I wrap it impeccably. And maybe I don’t tell them.’
lead_paragraph: LONDON — Jasmine Hemsley is a modern-day hunter, looking for treasures wearable, and often secondhand. Even, she insists, for gifts.

abstract: A selection of new nonfiction ranges from the plight of polar bears to the revitalization of Miami streets.
snippet: A selection of new nonfiction ranges from the plight of polar bears to the revitalization of Miami streets.
lead_paragraph: Search “sustainability” in Amazon’s book selection and you get more than 20,000 results — a lot to consider during the busy holiday shopping season. So, to help you make selections, here are a few noteworthy new books that look at the issue through animals, jewelry, fragrance and other topics.

abstract: From a baby carriage on a Manhattan street corner, she sold Southern food to African-Americans who, like her, had moved to New York during the Great Migration.

lead_paragraph: This article is part of Overlooked, a series of obituaries about remarkable people whose deaths, beginning in 1851, went unreported in The Times.

abstract: Mind-boggling pop-ups, a “Tintin” collection, a deluxe “Alice in Wonderland” and more gift-worthy children’s books that pack a visual punch.
snippet: Mind-boggling pop-ups, a “Tintin” collection, a deluxe “Alice in Wonderland” and more gift-worthy children’s books that pack a visual punch.
lead_paragraph: Before children learn to read, they learn to decipher pictures: smiling faces, furry animals, snowflakes. Even as they become fluid readers, using their imaginations to conjure images that the words leave out, that hunger for satisfying visuals never fades. Seductive color palettes, clever interplay of words and images, thoughtful paper craft — these are the factors that make illustrated books such desirable objects to read, touch and admire.

abstract: Don’t trade away your health data without considering the potential issues first.
snippet: Don’t trade away your health data without considering the potential issues first.
lead_paragraph: After I signed up for my insurance plan, I got an email with a link to a “wellness program” that, if I traded some health data — such as steps from a pedometer or smartwatch exercise data — could earn me a small monthly payout and some gift cards. But the second I logged in, I felt paranoid about the whole thing.
